HEADWORD: Coccygeal
<hw>Coc*cyg"e*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Of or pertaining to the coccyx; <as>as, the <ex>coccygeal</ex>
vertebr⟦ae⟧</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Coccygeal glands</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <cd>,
glands situated at the base of the tail of birds. They secrete the oil
with which the plumage is dressed.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coccygeous</ent>⟦br⟧
